# Traffic Light Simulator (Java)
This project contains a simple Java program that simulates traffic light actions.  
It asks the user to enter a traffic light color and displays the corresponding action.
## ðŸ“– Description
- Prompts the user to enter a traffic light color (`red`, `yellow`, or `green`)
- Uses if-else statements to display the corresponding action:
  - `"red"` OUTPUT:`"Stop"`
  - `"yellow"` OUTPUT:`"Slow Down"`
  - `"green"` OUTPUT:`"Go"`
- Handles invalid input by displaying an error message
- Demonstrates basic string comparison using `.equals()`
- ðŸ“Œ Learning Concepts
Using Scanner for user input
Conditional statements (if-else)
String comparison with .equals()
